response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Finding the Maximum Element\", \"description\": \"Write a function `find_maximum` that takes a list of integers as input and returns the maximum element in the list. You can assume the list will always contain at least one element.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef find_maximum(nums: list[int]) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `nums` (list[int]): A list of integers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the maximum integer in the input list.\", \"code\": \"def find_maximum(nums: list[int]) -> int:\\n    max_num = nums[0]\\n    for num in nums:\\n        if num > max_num:\\n            max_num = num\\n    return max_num\", \"tests\": [\"assert find_maximum([1, 5, 2, 8, 3]) == 8\", \"assert find_maximum([-5, -2, -8, -1]) == -1\", \"assert find_maximum([10]) == 10\"] }"
